\subtree{
\title{Success Criteria}
\p{A well-designed workflow skill:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Has When to Use AND When NOT to Use sections}
\li{[ ] Uses a recognizable pattern (routing, pipeline, linear, safety gate, or task-driven)}
\li{[ ] Numbers all phases with entry and exit criteria}
\li{[ ] Lists only the tools it actually uses (least privilege)}
\li{[ ] Keeps SKILL.md under 500 lines with details in references/workflows}
\li{[ ] Has no hardcoded paths (uses \code{\startverb {baseDir}\stopverb})}
\li{[ ] Has no broken file references}
\li{[ ] Has no reference chains (all links one hop from SKILL.md)}
\li{[ ] Includes a verification step at the end of the workflow}
\li{[ ] Has a description that triggers correctly (third-person, specific keywords)}
\li{[ ] Includes concrete examples for key instructions}
\li{[ ] Explains WHY, not just WHAT, for essential principles}
}
}
}